-- Bank of America no longer bidding for Lehman: report
-- 
-- Sun Sep 14, 2008 4:02pm EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2008/09/14/us-lehman-bofa-idUSWAT01004120080914

 

 WASHINGTON  (Reuters) - Bank of America is no longer in the bidding for troubled investment bank Lehman Brothers, Bloomberg Television reported on Sunday, citing a person familiar with the negotiations. 

 "I've just heard from a person familiar with the negotiations that Bank of America is no longer in the bidding for Lehman Brothers," a Bloomberg TV reporter said. (Reporting by  Tim Ahmann ; Editing by  Andrea Ricci )